## Design System
**REQUIRED**: Read `DESIGN.md` before touching any UI file.
- Colors: ONLY use tokens from DESIGN.md section 2
- Typography: follow theme guidance in DESIGN.md section 0 and 3
- Spacing: ONLY from the scale in section 4
- Components: follow patterns in section 5
- Motion: see theme guidance in DESIGN.md section 0

If you need a pattern not in DESIGN.md → STOP, propose the addition,
wait for approval, then implement.

## Coding Conventions
- Components in `src/components/`, one folder per component
- Use `cn()` util for conditional classes
- No inline styles, no Tailwind arbitrary values (`[#hex]`, `[18px]`)
- Images: `next/image`, priority only for hero, alt text always required

## Performance Targets
- Lighthouse Performance > 85 (mobile)
- LCP < 3s on 3G
- No CLS from media (reserve space before load)
- Total initial load < 3MB

## Accessibility
- All tap targets ≥ 44px (WCAG)
- Video/animation must respect `prefers-reduced-motion`
- Color contrast: minimum AA
- Forms: proper labels, keyboard navigable, inline error states

## Workflow
- Before commit: `pnpm precommit` (lint + typecheck + check:tokens)
- Test on mobile first
- Check on slow 3G — key interactions must remain usable

## Reference Files (read before coding)
- `DESIGN.md` — design system source of truth
- `GUARDRAILS.md` — learned constraints, failure patterns
- `docs/DESIGN-DECISIONS.md` — architectural decision log
